FILE OPERATION COMMANDS

 Get-Location (“ show current directory “)
Get-ChildItem (“list files”) or ls 
Cd foldername (“ change directory “)
Cd.. (“ go back 1 step back”)
New-Item -ItemType Directory-Name foldername (“make new directory “)
Remove -Item -ItemType File -Name filename.txt
————————————
File operations
New-Item -Item Type File -Name filename.txt.  (“Create a new text file”)
Add-Content  filename.txt “add content” (“write content to file”)
Get-Content filename.txt (“view file content”)
Copy -Item filename.txt new filename.txt (“copy file into new file”)
Move-Item filename.txt folder\ (“move file from 1 folder to other”)
Remove -Item filename.txt (“Remove file”)
————————————————-
USER & PERMISSIONS COMMANDS
whoami (“ show current user”)
Get-LocalUser (“ list all users”)
net user username newpassword (“ change password”)
icacls file.txt/grant User:F (“change file permission “)
takeown /f filename.txt (“ change file owner”)
———————————
Change laptop password using ps commands

Set-LocalUser -Name "YourUserName" -Password (Read-Host -AsSecureString "Enter New Password") (“change a Windows user account password (often referred to as the “laptop password”) 

Set-LocalUser -Name "TargetUserName" -Password (ConvertTo-SecureString "NewPasswordHere" -AsPlainText -Force) (“For Another Local User If you’re an administrator and want to reset another account’s password:”)
