————————————————
Create a hidden file
New-Item -Path C:\Temp\secret.txt -ItemType File -Force
Set-Content -Path C:\Temp\secret.txt -Value "Top secret content"
(Get-Item C:\Temp\secret.txt).Attributes += 'Hidden'
————-

echo Top secret content> C:\Temp\secret.txt
attrib +h C:\Temp\secret.txt
(“Write text and set Hidden attribute: ”)
——————-
New-Item -Path C:\Temp\HiddenFolder -ItemType Directory
(Get-Item C:\Temp\HiddenFolder).Attributes = 'Hidden'
(“Make a hidden folder (PowerShell”)

———————————-
TO CREAT A HIDDEN FILE / ADD CONTENT TO FILE / SEE CONTENT IN FILE / REMOVE HIDDEN FILE
1-Create an file
                                    New-Item -Path “url\filename.txt”

2-To create a file and need location of folder
                                                [Environment]::GetFolderPath("Desktop")     -This is to filnd desktop folder you can change Desktop into your required folder name

3-Hide created file
                                    Set-ItemProperty -Path “url\filename.txt” -Name Attribute -Value Hidden
4-Add content to hidden file 
                                    Add-Content -Path “url\filename.txt” -Value “add text content you want in the hidden file” 

5- see for hidden file
                                    Get-ChildItem -Path “url\filename.txt” -Force  Where-Object { $_.Attributes -math “Hidden”}

6- look content inside the file
                                    Get-Content -Path “url\filename.txt“

7-REMOVE OR DELETE FILE
                                    Remove -Item -Path “C:\Users\lapto\OneDrive\Desktop\filename.txt”
